Package space.arim.universal.util.proxy

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CaptiveReference<T>
    A simple implementation of ProxiedReference supplied with the proxied object at construction.
    DishonestMap<K,V>
    A ProxiedMap which does nothing other than change the result of calls to Map.get(Object).
    DishonestReference<T>
    A CaptiveReference which does nothing other than change the result of calls to DishonestReference.getValue().
    DynamicUnmodifiableCollection<E>
    A UnmodifiableCollection whose original, backing collection is dynamically provided by a Supplier.
    ProxiedCollection<E>
    A parent class for collections which simply redirect, a.k.a.
    ProxiedCompletableFuture<T>
    A parent class for completable futures which simply redirect, a.k.a.
    ProxiedConnection
    A parent class for connections which simply redirect, a.k.a.
    ProxiedIterator<E>
    A parent class for iterators which simply redirect, a.k.a proxy, calls to another iterator (the backing iterator).
    ProxiedList<E>
    A ProxiedCollection, specifically a List.
    ProxiedMap<K,V>
    A parent class for maps which simply redirect, a.k.a.
    ProxiedObject<T>
    A general parent object for objects, which simply redirect, a.k.a.
    ProxiedReference<T>
    A helper for proxying final objects.
    ProxiedSet<E>
    A ProxiedCollection, specifically a Set.
    UnmodifiableCollection<E>
    A ProxiedCollection which prohibits changes to the underlying, backing collection.
    UnmodifiableDishonestMap<K,V>
    An unmodifiable variant of DishonestMap.
    UnmodifiableIterator<E>
    A ProxiedIterator which does nothing other than throw UnsupportedOperationException on calls to UnmodifiableIterator.remove().
